==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Portulaca
<hw>Por`tu*la"ca</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.,
purslane.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A genus of polypetalous plants;
also, any plant of the genus.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ <spn>Portulaca oleracea</spn> is the common purslane.
<spn>Portulaca grandiflora</spn> is a South American herb, widely
cultivated for its showy crimson, scarlet, yellow, or white, ephemeral
blossoms.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Portulacaceous</ent>⟦br⟧
